  "prompt": "Is is easy to shift from Aero to mechatronics after the first year in mit, manipal? What cgpa is required?",
  "response": "Shifting branches at universities can often depend on various factors, including availability, academic performance, and departmental policies. At MIT, Manipal (now known as Manipal Institute of Technology, under Manipal Academy of Higher Education), branch changes are typically allowed after the first year, subject to certain conditions.\n\nUsually, branch changes are competitive and based on CGPA. While specific CGPA requirements for changing from Aeronautical Engineering to Mechatronics Engineering can vary from year to year based on demand and capacity, a high CGPA is generally required. In many instances, students looking to change branches aim for a CGPA of above 8.0 or 8.5 out of 10 to improve their chances, but again, this can vary.\n\nIn addition to having a solid CGPA, it\u2019s important to:\n\n1. **Meet any additional criteria** that the departments may set.\n2. **Apply within the given time frame** for branch changes.\n3. **Check if there are any seat availability constraints** in the desired branch.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, you should consult the academic handbook or speak directly with the academic advisors or administrative offices at MIT, Manipal. They will provide the specific criteria and process for a branch change.",
